# Shared cache/home runtime env for H200 Phase 1 systemd units.
#
# Installed to /etc/clypt/clypt-phase1-runtime.env (0644 root:root) by
# scripts/do_phase1_visual/deploy_visual_service.sh and referenced via
# EnvironmentFile= from these three units:
#   * clypt-v31-phase1-api.service
#   * clypt-v31-phase1-worker.service
#   * clypt-v31-phase24-local-worker.service
#
# These values match the previously-duplicated per-unit Environment=
# lines exactly; do not change the paths here without also updating
# docs/runtime/RUNTIME_GUIDE.md and AGENTS.md Runtime Truths
# (HF_HOME and TORCH_HOME paths must remain stable).
#
# Intentionally NOT used by:
#   * clypt-sglang-qwen.service — uses a different HF_HOME
#     (/opt/clypt-phase1/hf-cache) and has no HOME/TORCH_HOME/XDG_CACHE_HOME.
#     Leaving that unit's Environment= lines inline preserves its cache
#     layout and keeps HF_HUB_OFFLINE=1 plus SGLANG_ENABLE_SPEC_V2=1
#     co-located with the service that needs them.
#   * RTX-side units (clypt-audio-host.service, clypt-vllm-vibevoice.service)
#     — those live under /opt/clypt-audio-host with a different cache
#     layout and must not share this file.
#
# Syntax: systemd EnvironmentFile= uses bare KEY=VALUE, one per line,
# without the "Environment=" prefix that appears in unit files.
HOME=/opt/clypt-phase1
CLYPT_PHASE1_CACHE_HOME=/opt/clypt-phase1/.cache
XDG_CACHE_HOME=/opt/clypt-phase1/.cache
TORCH_HOME=/opt/clypt-phase1/.cache/torch
HF_HOME=/opt/clypt-phase1/.cache/huggingface
